<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-9406] hadoop-client leaks dependency on JDK tools jar</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-9406</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;hadoop-client leaks out JDK tools jar as dependency. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JDK tools jar is defined as a system dependency for hadoop-annotation/jdiff/javadocs purposes, if not done javadoc generation fails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that in the way it is defined now, this dependency ends up leaking to hadoop-client and downstream projects that depend on hadoop-client may end up including/bundling JDK tools JAR.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
